00:22:43.668 --> 00:22:48.648
Ellen: So that's the one she was just...in

00:22:48.648 --> 00:22:49.648
the video right?

00:22:49.648 --> 00:22:52.558
Diana: Yeah, so this is…these are just two

00:22:52.558 --> 00:22:54.617
different types of flashlights we use.

00:22:54.617 --> 00:23:02.528
This is just a regular flashlight, a good
intensity to look at surfaces of objects,

00:23:02.528 --> 00:23:06.138
to look for damages and things like that.

00:23:06.138 --> 00:23:10.587
And Ellen's holding a UV flashlight.

00:23:10.587 --> 00:23:12.837
So this tells us different types of information.

00:23:12.837 --> 00:23:16.648
Ellen: Yeah, shining a UV light on a surface

