00:27:37.098 --> 00:27:39.258
Ellen: That's a really great invention.

00:27:39.258 --> 00:27:41.867
I think you're sitting on a million-dollar
idea.

00:27:41.867 --> 00:27:45.467
Diana: And then this is just an example of

00:27:45.467 --> 00:27:50.598
a palette we use with some gambling conservation
colors.

00:27:50.598 --> 00:27:56.117
We use all different types of paints, depending
on what we're working on.

00:27:56.117 --> 00:27:57.117
Ellen: Why is it gray?

00:27:57.117 --> 00:27:58.278
Diana: So it's gray.

00:27:58.278 --> 00:28:03.857
Gray kind of helps you see…it's not stark
